==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glede
<hw>Glede</hw> <pr>(gl⟦emac⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>glida</ets>, akin to Icel. <ets>gle⟦edh⟧a</ets>, Sw.
<ets>glada</ets>. Cf. <er>Glide</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The common European kite (<spn>Milvus
ictinus</spn>). This name is also sometimes applied to the
buzzard.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>glead</asp>, <asp>gled</asp>,
<asp>gleed</asp>, <asp>glade</asp>, and <asp>glide</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glede</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Glede
<hw>Glede</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Gleed</er>.]</ety> <def>A
live coal.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The cruel ire, red as any <qex>glede</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

